  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    gov.nasa.worldwind.avlist.AVList, gov.nasa.worldwind.Disposable, gov.nasa.worldwind.drag.Draggable, gov.nasa.worldwind.Locatable, gov.nasa.worldwind.Movable, gov.nasa.worldwind.render.Annotation, gov.nasa.worldwind.render.Renderable, gov.nasa.worldwind.Restorable, java.io.Serializable

    public class ToggleAnnotation
extends gov.nasa.worldwind.render.GlobeAnnotation
implements java.io.Serializable
    Map annotations that can be "toggled" with a mouse click.
    WARNING! NOT ALL FIELDS ARE SERIALIZED!
    Serialized fields are ONLY: _selectedText, _unselectedText, position, minActiveAltitude, maxActiveAltitude
    Currently, the attributes are NOT serialized.
    Author:
    Scott Rixner, Stephen Wong
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • setSelectedBackgroundColor

        public void setSelectedBackgroundColor(java.awt.Color c)
        Sets the background color to use when the annotation is selected. To set the unselected background color, use the inherited getAttributes().setBackgroundColor(Color c). The annotation must be unselected to set the unselected background color. The selected background color can be set at any time.
        Parameters:
        c - The background color to use when selected.
